result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathaniel D Grosbeier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While Revoked (Misdemeanor)], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Nathaniel D Grosbeier in court with attorney James Creviere Foote.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant Nathaniel D Grosbeier in court with attorney James Creviere Foote.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 1 & 2.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Cts. 1 & 2. Court dismisses Cts. 3 & 4 but reads in for sentencing. Atty Foote asks court to set off sentencing until late January. State has no objection. Bond remains in effect.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 28, 2016 at 11:00 am.
Do not operate a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license and subject to any conditions or restrictions on that license.  To be fingerprinted and photographed before next court date.

Defendant Nathaniel D Grosbeier in court with attorney James Creviere Foote.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel. Defense waives reading of the complaint, enters not guilty plea. Court finds probable cause for bindover. State requests cash bond. Defense gives argument. Bond set.  Status conference scheduled for November 6, 2015 at 11:00 am.
